OL,7,FWestminster Magistrates' Court heard
OL,8,FGill allegedly made statements in the
OL,9,FEuropean Parliament and in opinion
OL,10,Fpieces to news outlets, such as 112
OL,11,FUkraine, which were "supportive of a
OL,12,Fparticular narrative" which would
OL,13,F"benefit Russia regarding events in
OL,14,FUkraine".
OL,16,FThe defendant is alleged to have been
OL,17,Ftasked by Oleg Voloshyn on at least
OL,18,Feight occasions to make specific
OL,19,Fstatements in return for money.
